<center><h1> Introduction (Contd) </h1></center>

<h2>

<u> Motivation </u>

 Dissatisfaction in users since most of the applications have no
knowledge about the user's real world situation and they are conventionally
developed to provide explicit functionalities.



<u> Definition </u>

Situated Computing is an activity-centered paradigm to enhance the
user's interaction in mobile environment through applications that can
understand the user's context and activities.



<u> Key terms </u>
<ul>
<li> Entity : 

              A logical piece of information in a situation  </li> 

<li> Metaphor:

              A statement which serves as means of making an un-known
                  complexity into an understandable format.</li>

<li> Activity:

              A particular engagement or action of the user in a situation 
</li>        


</h2>






